name: Featherweight stretcher -09
description:
Fits in:
1 fully loaded soldier
Fits inside:
Trauma pouch
Features:
An extremely light weight stretcher that always can be attached to the medic bag

Very light weight (500 g)
Small storage space, fits in a magazine pouch or similar (10x 10x 5 cm)
The best pouch to carry it is the Trauma pouch
Strong enough to carry a fully loaded soldier (150 kg)
Can be used as a sledge (the fabric might break but the patient will stay on it)
6 handles
2 channels for carrying poles (from the forest)

name: Foldable drinking cup
description:
Durable plastic cup pops open from its folded position to form an 2 dl drinking cup.
Guaranteed not to leak, even with boiling water.
The best cup to bring into the field.
Always carry it in one of your trouser pockets so it is easy to reach when you want to drink from a stream.
Snigel logo printed on the outside.

name: Plastic bag, ziplock A6 -09, 10 pack
description:
A thick plastic bag with zip lock closure.
The bag is 4 times as thick as a normal plastic bag.
10 bags are sold together.
For your note book, wallet, mobile, toilet paper or similar.
When you open it, dont just pull. Rather, insert your finger tips in the middle of the zipper and push at the same time that you pull the zipper apart.

name: Sleeping bag cover with hood 2.0
description:
A lightweight sleeping bag cover designed to ensure a comfortable night’s sleep for soldiers in any weather and at any location within their sleeping bag.
FEATURES

A light weight sleeping bag cover with a hood and zipped access, to protect your sleeping bag.
Velcro patch by the opening and in the bottom where you can attach a name plate to identify you, so the correct soldier is awakened for duty in the night.
Removable mosquito net attached with a zipper.
Elastic cord around the opening.
Zipper with flaps on the left side.
All seams are taped.
